Notes: The context seems to refer to cutting lines (i.e. clearing scrub etc) for a tunnel (p128) poss. short for `railway linesmen' - in Northland; a roadman; one who clears edges of roads, gutters, etc; a (county or MOW) road worker (? from one who looks after a line n1.); ? lines- used mainly in or felt as a pluralising agent linesmen.
